cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

This paper focuses on generating persona consistent dialogues using natural language inference (NLI) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes an attention-based encoder-decoder model, which is a common technique in deep learning and falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates its approach using automatic metrics, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval and ranking of responses, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
